#
#   STAGE 3 — GAZE VELOCITY & ACCELERATION
#
#       3a. Convert GAZE_DIR Euler angles (X,Y,Z) -> unit vectors   
#       3b. Compute angular displacement (AD) between consecutive samples
#       3c. Divide AD by time delta -> velocity (degrees/second)
#       3d. Compute change in velocity between samples -> acceleration
#       3e. Apply Savitzky-Golay smoothing to velocity signal
#
#   STAGE 4 — EVENT CLASSIFICATION (Nyström & Holmqvist, 2010)
#
#       4a. Compute adaptive velocity threshold from noise characteristics
#       4b. Classify each sample: saccade/glissade/fixation candidate
#       4c. Merge glissades into preceeding saccade (glissade policy)
#       4d. Apply minimum duration filter to fixations (ca. 100ms/ 6 samples)
#       4e. Output: every sample labeled as fixation / saccade / excluded
#
#   STAGE 5 — AOI FIXATION AGGREGATION
#
#       5a. For each fixation event, assign object label (majority vote)
#       5b. Classify fixation as task-relevant / task-irrelevant / neither
#           -> relevant   : object is on shopping list for this condition
#           -> irrelevant : object is not on shopping list for this condition
#           -> neither    : OBJECT = "nothing"
#       5c. Compute per-condition eye-tracking metrics:
