#           -> Number of fixations on relevant vs irrrelevant items
#           -> Mean fixation duration on relevant vs irrelevant items
#           -> Saccade rate (saccaddes per second)
#           -> Saccade count (total, and between relevant items specifically)
#     
#   STAGE 6 — TASK PERFORMANCE
#
#       6a. Separate picks into correct (OBJECT_ON_LIST = TRUE)
#                           and incorrect (OBJECT_ON_LIST = FALSE)
#       6b. Performance score = correct picks / 7
#       6c. Grab accuracy = correct picks / total picks
#           -> sensitive measure of accidental grabbing
#       6d. Task completion time = last timestamp - first timestamp
#
#   STAGE 7 — OUTPUT
#   
#       7a. Combine all metrics into one row per participant X condition
